etymology.description: pictogram: wine jar (ancient/variant form of 酉).
etymology.interpretation: Depicts a wine vessel with a stopper, the same object later standardized as 酉. By extension it served as the 10th Earthly Branch, associated with the dusk period and the west.

examples.chinese: 古籍里，丣是地支的第十位，对应傍晚的酉时(古籍裡，丣是地支的第十位，對應傍晚的酉時)。
examples.pinyin: Gǔjí lǐ, yǒu shì dìzhī de dì shí wèi, duìyìng bàngwǎn de yǒu shí.
examples.english: In old texts, 丣 is the tenth Earthly Branch, corresponding to the evening You hour.

examples.chinese: 在甲骨文研究中，丣常被解释为盛酒的器形(在甲骨文研究中，丣常被解釋為盛酒的器形)。
examples.pinyin: Zài jiǎgǔwén yánjiū zhōng, yǒu cháng bèi jiěshì wéi shèng jiǔ de qìxíng.
examples.english: In oracle-bone studies, 丣 is often interpreted as the shape of a wine vessel.

examples.chinese: 这个古字偶尔出现在历法术语和古文献中(這個古字偶爾出現在曆法術語和古文獻中)。
examples.pinyin: Zhège gǔzì ǒu'ěr chūxiàn zài lìfǎ shùyǔ hé gǔ wénxiàn zhōng.
examples.english: This archaic character occasionally appears in calendrical terminology and classical literature.
